                <head type="CCC">pseudo-Albertus Magnus OP, Lapidarium. Prognostication Tracts</head>
                <head type="James">Ps.-Albertus de Lapidibus etc.</head>

                <p function="Codicology"><material>Vellum</material>, <measureGrp type="CCC">
                        <height unit="mm">190</height>
                        <width unit="mm">125</width>
                    </measureGrp>, <measureGrp type="James">7.4 x 5.3</measureGrp>, <extent>ff. 1 + 58 + 17</extent>,
                        <layout>two volumes, 24 and 21 lines to a page</layout>. Cent. <origDate>xiii -xiv</origDate>
                    and <origDate>xv</origDate>.</p>

                <p function="Multivolume" rend="withinContents"><lb/><label>Volume I:</label>
                    <handNote>In a very neat hand, probably Italian</handNote>. <lb/><label>Volume II:</label>
                    <handNote>In a very ugly current hand</handNote>.</p>

                <p><label>Collation:</label>
                    <collation>1 flyleaf, 1<num>8</num>-7<num>8</num> 8<num>2</num> | ff. 17</collation>.</p>

                <p><label>2 fo.:</label>
                    <secFol>Aghates</secFol>.</p>

                <p function="Provenance">On flyleaf <supplied>(f. <locus>ivr</locus>)</supplied>: <name type="person"
                        >Jane Knukle</name>.</p>

                <p type="CCC">
                    <foliation>ff. i-iv + 1-75 + v-vi</foliation>.</p>

                <msContents>

                    <textLang mainLang="lat">Latin.</textLang>
                    <label>Contents</label>

                    <milestone n="I" unit="volume"/>

                    <msItem n="1" locusStart="1r" locusEnd="58v">
                        <head type="CCC">
                            <name type="author">pseudo-Albertus Magnus OP</name>, <title>Lapidarium</title>
                        </head>

                        <rubric locus="1r">Incipit liber de coloribus et uirtutibus lapidum. Liber primus</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="1r">Habete celi silentium et ingratitudinis in mane scelus
                            attendite</incipit>
                        <explicit locusNew="1v">renuente uero quasi non editus uel oblitus fueris habeatis</explicit>
                        <ab locus="1v">Prologue</ab>
                        <incipit locusNew="1v">Substantie mi liber gemme mellifluis arride decoloribus</incipit>
                        <explicit locusNew="1v">ut irrigatur ortus flamine diuini spiritus animatus agnoscat graciam qua
                            fertile se retribuat</explicit>
                        <rubric locusNew="1v">Tractatus de a. prima lictera de omnibus lapidibus</rubric>
                        <rubric locusNew="1v">De amante</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="1v">Adamantum genus eximium cristalizat quodammodo</incipit>
                        <ab>Stones are treated alphabetically. The last is yctios, ending</ab>
                        <explicit locus="20v">ac more paragoni confricati metalli colorem retinet</explicit>
                        <rubric locus="20v">De sculturis de omnibus lapidibus</rubric>
                        <ab>Liber II</ab>
                        <rubric locus="21v">de natione et ubi inueniuntur</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="21v">Post autem facilius preuia discretione</incipit>
                        <ab>Liber III</ab>
                        <rubric locus="27r">de sculturis lapidum</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="27r">Quod non inuida philosophorum largitio</incipit>
                        <ab>Liber IV</ab>
                        <rubric locus="40v">de consecratione lapidum</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="40v">Aperuit thesauros dominus mirifice</incipit>
                        <ab>Liber V</ab>
                        <rubric locus="44r">de confectione et compositione lapidum</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="44r">Paulisper equidem euagari si liceat</incipit>
                        <ab>Ends</ab>
                        <explicit locus="58v">Actenus hec omnia discrete protendisse sufficiat ut nec uulgari se doleant
                            nec omnino deparant silentio reticenda</explicit>
                        <rubric locusNew="58v">Finite libro sit laus et gloria Christo. Amen</rubric>
                        <rubric locusNew="58v">Explicit liber lapidum</rubric>

                        <ab>The treatise is attributed (falsely) to <name type="person">Albertus Magnus</name>. Another
                            copy is among the Hunterian MSS. at <ref type="ms" target="GHL468">Glasgow, V 6,
                            18</ref></ab>



                    </msItem>

                    <milestone n="II" unit="volume"/>

                    <msItem n="2" locusStart="59r" locusEnd="75r">
                        <head type="CCC">
                            <title>Prognostication tracts</title>
                        </head>

                        <incipit locus="1r" locusNew="59r">Ad cognicionem tabule planetarum habendam intrandum est cum
                            die in capite</incipit>
                        <incipit locus="15r" locusNew="73r">Ad cognoscendum gradus caliditatis et siccitatis</incipit>
                        <ab>Ends <locus locusNew="74r">16r</locus> unfinished</ab>
                        <ab>On <locus locusNew="75r">17r</locus>, 12 lines <handNote>in another hand</handNote></ab>
                        <incipit locusNew="75r">
                            <lg>
                                <l>Elpes dicta fui sicule regionis alumpna</l>
                                <l>Quam procull a patria coniugis egit amor. </l>
                            </lg>
                        </incipit>

                        <explicit locusNew="75r">
                            <lg>
                                <l>Ut tulerim tumulique comes nec morte reueller</l>
                                <l>Et socies uite nectat (?) utrumque cinis.</l>
                            </lg>
                        </explicit>

                        <ab>(Epitaph of <name type="person">Elpis</name>, wife of <name type="person">Boethius</name>;
                            two hymns are current under her name)</ab>

                    </msItem>

                </msContents>
